Following the frequent kidnapping in Kaduna State and its environs, the state government has directed the immediate closure of all schools in Kajuru Local Government Area. In a circular signed by Abigail D. Adza, Quality Assurance Officer, Ministry of Education, Kaduna State, dated 16th March, 2021, directed all principals, private Public and head teachers in Kajuru LGA, all schools should close with immediate effect. The circular reads: ” The Director General Kaduna state Ministry of Education, quality assurance has directed me to inform all proprietors and principals of both private and public schools in Kajuru LGA to close down all schools with immediate effect from today, 16/3/2021.” “No school should reopen, until you are told to do so. Be security conscious,” it said